BOOT_NORMAL

public static final int BOOT_NORMAL
causes the system to go through the countdown sequence and try to reboot VxWorks automatically. Memory is not cleared.

reboot

public static void reboot(int how)
Reboot cRIO WARNING: Only use BOOT_CLEAR. Otherwise 5% chance of error on reboot.

Parameters:

javaDelay

public static void javaDelay(int ticks)
Delay the Java VM. Calls taskDelay for the given number of ticks. WARNING: Only use if C/C++ tasks are getting starved. For ordinary delays use Timer.delay() or Thread.sleep().

Parameters:
ticks - (1 tick == 16ms)

javaYield

public static void javaYield()
Have all Java threads yield the CPU to native threads. WARNING: Only use if C/C++ tasks are getting starved. For ordinary yield use Thread.yield().

kernelTimeSlice

public static void kernelTimeSlice(int ticks)
Set the vxworks time slice for round-robin scheduling of same-priority tasks. Setting to zero will disable round-robin (bad!)

Parameters:
ticks - (1 tick == 16ms)
